{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Timothy 2 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:1",
      "text": "You then, my son, be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:2",
      "text": "and what you have heard from me before many witnesses entrust to faithful men who will be able to teach others also.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:3",
      "text": "Share in suffering as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:4",
      "text": "No soldier on service gets entangled in civilian pursuits, since his aim is to satisfy the one who enlisted him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:5",
      "text": "An athlete is not crowned unless he competes according to the rules.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:6",
      "text": "It is the hard-working farmer who ought to have the first share of the crops.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:7",
      "text": "Think over what I say, for the Lord will grant you understanding in everything.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:8",
      "text": "Remember Jesus Christ, risen from the dead, descended from David, as preached in my gospel,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:9",
      "text": "the gospel for which I am suffering and wearing fetters like a criminal. But the word of God is not fettered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:10",
      "text": "Therefore I endure everything for the sake of the elect, that they also may obtain salvation in Christ Jesus with its eternal glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:11",
      "text": "The saying is sure: If we have died with him, we shall also live with him;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:12",
      "text": "if we endure, we shall also reign with him; if we deny him, he also will deny us;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:13",
      "text": "if we are faithless, he remains faithful— for he cannot deny himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:14",
      "text": "Remind them of this, and charge them before the Lord to avoid disputing about words, which does no good, but only ruins the hearers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:15",
      "text": "Do your best to present yourself to God as one approved, a workman who has no need to be ashamed, rightly handling the word of truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:16",
      "text": "Avoid such godless chatter, for it will lead people into more and more ungodliness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:17",
      "text": "and their talk will eat its way like gangrene. Among them are Hymenaeus and Philetus,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:18",
      "text": "who have swerved from the truth by holding that the resurrection is past already. They are upsetting the faith of some.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:19",
      "text": "But God's firm foundation stands, bearing this seal: “The Lord knows those who are his,” and, “Let every one who names the name of the Lord depart from iniquity.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:20",
      "text": "In a great house there are not only vessels of gold and silver but also of wood and earthenware, and some for noble use, some for ignoble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:21",
      "text": "If any one purifies himself from what is ignoble, then he will be a vessel for noble use, consecrated and useful to the master of the house, ready for any good work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:22",
      "text": "So shun youthful passions and aim at righteousness, faith, love, and peace, along with those who call upon the Lord from a pure heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:23",
      "text": "Have nothing to do with stupid, senseless controversies; you know that they breed quarrels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:24",
      "text": "And the Lord's servant must not be quarrelsome but kindly to every one, an apt teacher, forbearing,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:25",
      "text": "correcting his opponents with gentleness. God may perhaps grant that they will repent and come to know the truth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.2.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:26",
      "text": "and they may escape from the snare of the devil, after being captured by him to do his will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
